()QueryOptions SailPoint me database query ko filter karne ke liye use hota hai.
Matlab jab hum getObjects() ya search() use karte hain, tab QueryOptions batata hai ki kaunsa data chahiye. 😎

1️⃣ QueryOptions kya hai?
QueryOptions = query ke rules / filters
Ye decide karta hai:-
Kaunsa object chahiye
Kaunsa condition apply karna hai
Kitne records chahiye
Sorting kaise hogi

one line:-QueryOptions class SailPoint me database query ko control karne ke liye use hoti hai.
Isme kuch important methods hote hain jisse hum filter, limit, sorting, pagination control karte hain.

1️⃣ addFilter(Filter filter):-
Query me filter condition add karta hai.
QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("department","Finance"));

2️⃣ setFilters(List filters):-
Multiple filters ek saath set karta hai.
List filters = new ArrayList();
filters.add(Filter.eq("department","IT"));
filters.add(Filter.eq("status","Active"));
qo.setFilters(filters);

3️⃣ getFilters():-
Jo filters lagaye gaye hain unki list return karta hai.
List filters = qo.getFilters();

4️⃣ setDistinct(boolean distinct):-
Duplicate results remove karta hai.
qo.setDistinct(true);

5️⃣ setPageSize(int size):-
Ek baar me kitne records fetch honge.
qo.setPageSize(50);
Meaning:-
50 records per page

6️⃣ setFirstRow(int row):-
Pagination ke liye start row define karta hai.
qo.setFirstRow(10);
Meaning:-
10th record se data lana

7️⃣ setResultLimit(int limit):-
Maximum kitne records return honge.
qo.setResultLimit(100);
Meaning:-
Maximum 100 records

8️⃣ addOrdering(String field, boolean ascending):-
Sorting apply karta hai.
qo.addOrdering("name", true);
Meaning:-
name ascending order me

9️⃣ setCacheResults(boolean cache):-
Kya karta hai:-
Ye decide karta hai ki query ka result cache me store hoga ya nahi.
Agar cache enable hai to next time same query run hogi to database se nahi, cache se result milega.
Example:-
QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
qo.setCacheResults(true);

🔟 setCloneResults(boolean clone)
Kya karta hai?
Ye result objects ka clone copy return karta hai.
Matlab:-
Original object safe rahega
Returned object ek copy hoga

1️⃣1️⃣ setIgnoreCase(boolean ignore)
Kya karta hai?
Ye case sensitive search ko ignore karta hai.
Matlab:-
Rahul
rahul
RAHUL
sab match ho jayenge.

Example:-
QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
qo.setIgnoreCase(true);
qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("name","rahul"));

Result:-
rahul
Rahul
RAHUL